Description: Almost complete fragment of an ear- or hair-ring made of stone, broken off at one end, with a angular edges, triangular in section. On both sides a circumferential line, at the edge perpendicular small parallel lines. The stone is beige with black, partly red, breccia?
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E12.1, north section
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 176)
